<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The calls to strstr(filename, "..") and strchr(filename, '/') / strchr(filename, '\u005C') assume that filename points to a null-terminated string. If filename is not NUL-terminated (or otherwise not guaranteed to be a C string of known bounds), these functions will scan past the object’s bounds, causing out-of-bounds accesses. Although the code checks for filename == NULL earlier, it does not validate that filename is NUL-terminated or that the buffer length is sufficient. Example violation: filename points to a buffer of length N without a terminating '\0' (e.g. filled from untrusted input), so strstr/strchr will read beyond that buffer. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17 unless an external guarantee of NUL-termination is provided.
</scenario>

